00:44:48,040 --> 00:44:52,160
...like the Declaration of Independence
says to, when the old one don't work.

689
00:44:52,400 --> 00:44:55,520
Just a bit farther out West.

690
00:44:55,800 --> 00:44:57,760
An American naturalist wrote:

691
00:44:58,000 --> 00:45:01,080
"A patriot must always be ready
to defend his country...

692
00:45:01,320 --> 00:45:04,640
...against its government."

693
00:45:04,720 --> 00:45:07,240
I'd hate to be in your shoes today.

694
00:45:07,480 --> 00:45:13,000
You have a lot to think about. You've seen
evidence the public hasn't seen.

695
00:45:13,080 --> 00:45:15,840
Going back to when we were children...

696
00:45:16,080 --> 00:45:21,560
...I think most of us in this courtroom
thought justice came automatically.

697
00:45:21,800 --> 00:45:23,600
That virtue was its own reward.

698
00:45:23,840 --> 00:45:26,640
That good triumphs over evil.

699
00:45:26,880 --> 00:45:30,280
But as we get older
we know this isn't true.

700
00:45:30,520 --> 00:45:35,680
Individual human beings have to create
justice, and this is not easy...

701
00:45:35,920 --> 00:45:39,040
...because the truth often poses a threat
to power...

702
00:45:39,280 --> 00:45:42,720
...and one often has to fight power
at great risk to themselves.

703
00:45:42,960 --> 00:45:45,120
People like S.M. Holland...

704
00:45:45,360 --> 00:45:46,920
...Lee Bowers...

705
00:45:47,160 --> 00:45:48,640
...Jean Hill, Willie O'Keefe...

706
00:45:48,880 --> 00:45:51,960
...have all taken that risk
and they've all come forward.

707
00:45:52,200 --> 00:45:55,760
I have here some $8,000 in these letters...

708
00:45:56,000 --> 00:45:58,280
...sent from all over the country.

709
00:45:58,520 --> 00:46:01,480
Quarters, dimes, dollars from housewives...

710
00:46:01,720 --> 00:46:05,360
...plumbers, car salesmen,
teachers, invalids.

711
00:46:05,600 --> 00:46:09,520
These are people who cannot afford
to send money but do.

712
00:46:09,760 --> 00:46:11,800
People who drive cabs...

713
00:46:12,040 --> 00:46:13,440
...who nurse in hospitals...

714
00:46:13,680 --> 00:46:17,080
...who see their kids go to Vietnam.

715
00:46:17,320 --> 00:46:19,840
Why?

716
00:46:19,840 --> 00:46:21,920
Because they care.

717
00:46:22,160 --> 00:46:24,600
Because they want to know the truth.

718
00:46:24,840 --> 00:46:26,720
Because they want their country back.

719
00:46:26,960 --> 00:46:29,120
Because it still belongs to us...

720
00:46:29,360 --> 00:46:34,760
...as long as the people have the guts
to fight for what they believe in.

721
00:46:35,520 --> 00:46:40,160
The truth is the most important value
we have, because if it doesn't endure...

722
00:46:40,400 --> 00:46:42,080
...if the government murders truth...

723
00:46:42,320 --> 00:46:44,360
...if we cannot respect these people...

724
00:46:44,600 --> 00:46:50,920
...then this is not the country I was born in,
or the country I want to die in.

725
00:46:51,240 --> 00:46:52,320
Tennyson wrote:

726
00:46:52,560 --> 00:46:56,120
"Authority forgets a dying king."

727
00:46:56,320 --> 00:46:58,680
This was never more true
than for John F. Kennedy...

728
00:46:58,920 --> 00:47:02,440
...whose murder was probably one
of the most terrible moments...

729
00:47:02,680 --> 00:47:06,240
...in the history of our country.

730
00:47:07,160 --> 00:47:12,480
We, the people, the jury system sitting
in judgment on Clay Shaw...

731
00:47:12,760 --> 00:47:14,240
...represent the hope...

732
00:47:14,480 --> 00:47:17,920
...of humanity against government power.

733
00:47:18,160 --> 00:47:20,360
In discharging your duty...

734
00:47:20,600 --> 00:47:23,840
...to bring a first conviction
in this house of cards...

735
00:47:24,080 --> 00:47:26,040
...against Clay Shaw...

736
00:47:26,280 --> 00:47:31,040
"...ask not what your country can do for
you but what you can do for your country."

737
00:47:31,280 --> 00:47:33,120
Do not forget...

738
00:47:33,360 --> 00:47:36,560
...your dying king.

739
00:47:36,560 --> 00:47:38,280
Show this world...

740
00:47:38,520 --> 00:47:44,640
...this is still a government "of the people,
for the people and by the people."

741
00:47:45,680 --> 00:47:47,400
Nothing as long as you live...

742
00:47:47,640 --> 00:47:51,080
...will ever be more important.

743
00:47:52,640 --> 00:47:55,440
It's up to you.

744
00:48:16,200 --> 00:48:18,560
Has the jury reached a verdict?

745
00:48:18,800 --> 00:48:19,840
We have, Your Honor.

746
00:48:20,080 --> 00:48:23,880
Please hand the verdict to the clerk.

747
00:48:31,600 --> 00:48:35,360
Will the defendant please rise?

748
00:48:37,840 --> 00:48:40,480
The clerk will now read the verdict.

749
00:48:40,720 --> 00:48:44,960
"New Orleans, Louisiana. March 1, 1969."

750
00:48:45,200 --> 00:48:51,320
"We, the jury, find the defendant,
Clay Shaw, not guilty."

751
00:49:10,600 --> 00:49:12,120
We believe there was a conspiracy.

752
00:49:12,360 --> 00:49:15,080
Whether Shaw was a part of it
is another kettle of fish.

753
00:49:15,320 --> 00:49:18,200
There's Jim!

754
00:49:19,160 --> 00:49:25,400
Do you agree that this is a full vindication
of the Warren Commission?

755
00:49:25,600 --> 00:49:28,600
It only proves you cannot run
an investigation...

756
00:49:28,840 --> 00:49:33,120
...questioning the intelligence operations
of the US government.

757
00:49:33,360 --> 00:49:36,640
People claim you're unfit to hold office...

758
00:49:36,880 --> 00:49:38,960
...that you've ruined
Clay Shaw's reputation.

759
00:49:39,200 --> 00:49:40,440
Are you going to resign?

760
00:49:40,680 --> 00:49:44,360
Hell, no! I'm going to run again,
and I'm going to win!

761
00:49:44,600 --> 00:49:46,280
Who will you persecute next?

762
00:49:46,520 --> 00:49:49,320
If it takes me 30 years to nail every one
of the assassins...

763
00:49:49,560 --> 00:49:52,680
...then I will continue for 30 years!

764
00:49:52,920 --> 00:49:55,560
I owe that to Jack Kennedy
and the country.

765
00:49:55,800 --> 00:49:58,320
There's Clay! There's Clay Shaw!

766
00:49:58,560 --> 00:50:01,800
- How does it feel to be acquitted?
- It's been exhausting.

767
00:50:02,040 --> 00:50:03,000
What'll you do now?

768
00:50:03,240 --> 00:50:04,760
I'm going home and cook some étouffée.

769
00:50:05,000 --> 00:50:07,800
Were you confident about the outcome?

770
00:50:09,480 --> 00:50:14,360
- Do you think Garrison will be back?
- I'm sure he will.

771
00:50:20,600 --> 00:50:23,400
In 1979, RICHARD HELMS,
Director of Covert Operations in 1963,

772
00:50:23,640 --> 00:50:26,280
admitted under oath
that CLAY SHAW had worked for the CIA.

773
00:50:26,520 --> 00:50:29,360
CLAY SHAW died in 1974 of lung cancer.
No autopsy was allowed.

774
00:50:29,600 --> 00:50:33,400
In 1978, JIM GARRISON was elected Judge
of the Louisiana State Court of Appeal

775
00:50:33,640 --> 00:50:35,600
in New Orleans. He was re-elected in 1988.

776
00:50:35,840 --> 00:50:39,800
To this date, he has brought the only
public prosecution in the Kennedy killing.

